revision.text:
'''Combined Exhibition of Advanced Technologies''' <ref>{{cite web | url = http://exhibitors.ceatec.com/en/2005/common/com_pre.html | title = About CEATEC Japan | publisher = CEATEC Japan organizing committee |year= 2005 | accessdate = 2007-11-25 | quote = CEATEC JAPAN (Combined Exhibition of Advanced Technologies) is the largest international exhibition in Asia for the technology and electronics sectors, including the fields of imaging, information, and communications.}}</ref> (also known as CEATEC) is an annual [[trade show]]<ref>{{cite news | url = http://money.cnn.com/2006/10/05/technology/pluggedin_Lewis_CEATEC.fortune/index.htm | title = Domo arigato, Mr. Penguin-boton | publisher = CNNMoney |date= 2005-08-06 | accessdate = 2007-11-25 | quote = The annual trade show known as Combined Exhibition of Advanced Technologies (CEATEC) [...] | first=Peter | last=Lewis}}</ref> in [[Japan]]. It is regarded as the Japanese equivalent of [[Consumer Electronics Show]].<ref>{{cite news | url = http://money.cnn.com/2006/10/05/technology/pluggedin_Lewis_CEATEC.fortune/index.htm | title = Domo arigato, Mr. Penguin-boton | publisher = CNNMoney |date= 2005-08-06 | accessdate = 2007-11-25 | quote = The [...] (CEATEC) [...] is the Japanese equivalent of the Consumer Electronics Show (CES)[...]. | first=Peter | last=Lewis}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.news.com/2102-1083_3-6123442.html?tag=st.util.print | title = Week in review: On land and Ceatec | author = Michelle Meyers | publisher = cnet News.com |date= 2005-08-06 | accessdate = 2007-11-25 | quote = Japan's answer to the Consumer Electronics Show in the United States, the weeklong Ceatec (Combined Exhibition of Advanced Technologies) show [...]}}</ref> It is Japan's largest [[Information technology|IT]] and [[electronics]] exhibition and conference.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.eetimes.com/news/semi/showArticle.jhtml?articleID=216500223 | title = Android set-tops, TVs, VoIP phones are coming | author = Junko Yoshida | publisher = EETimes |date= 2009-04-10 | accessdate = 2009-08-17 | quote = This fall at CEATEC, Japan's largest electronics show, displays will include prototype Android set tops "conceptualized by Open Embedded Software Foundation (OESF)," according to the group's chairman Masataka Miura.}}</ref>
== History == The show is held every year in October in [[Makuhari Messe]] since the first CEATEC in 2000.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ceatec.com/2007_pre/en/ | title = CEATEC JAPAN 2007 - Event Information | publisher = CEATEC Japan Organizing Committee | accessdate = 2007-11-25 | quote = The annual trade show known as Combined Exhibition of Advanced Technologies (CEATEC) [...]}}</ref> The most recent exhibition, the ninth iteration of CEATEC, was held between September 30 to October 4, 2008.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ceatec.com/<!-- Please provide citation outside CEATEC, if possible --> | title = CEATEC JAPAN 2008 | accessdate = 2008-10-19 }}</ref> CEATEC Japan 2008, attracted nearly 197,000 visitors, with some 804 exhibitors and 138 seminars.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ceatec.com/2008/en/press_media/press_release/ceatec_detail.html?press_type=office&press_id=00053 <!-- Please provide citation outside CEATEC, if possible --> | title = CEATEC JAPAN 2008 Concludes | author = CEATEC | publisher = CEATEC (Press release) |date= 2008-10-04 | accessdate = 2009-08-17 | quote = A total of 804 companies and organizations exhibited in 3,121 booth spaces, including 289 exhibitors from 27 countries and regions around the world. The exhibition drew 196,630 registered visitors in the five days it was open.}}</ref> Attendance was down from the almost 206,000 people and 895 companies in 2007<ref>{{cite web | url = http://news.cnet.com/8301-11386_3-10052373-76.html?tag=mncol;title | title = Ceatec: Gadget hounds, get ready | author = Erica Ogg | publisher = cnet |date= 2008-09-29 | accessdate = 2009-08-17 | quote = It's a huge show: just less than 206,000 people showed up to see the 895 companies show off their wares last year. The 2008 confab, which runs from Tuesday to Friday in Chiba, Japan, just outside Tokyo, promises to be even bigger.}}</ref> as it apparently felt the crunch of the [[financial crisis of 2007–2010]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://news.cnet.com/8301-1001_3-10056392-92.html?tag=txt | title = Ceatec companies feeling the credit crunch | author = Erica Ogg | publisher = cnet |date= 2008-10-02 | accessdate = 2009-08-17}}</ref>
