{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox brand |name=Panaglide |image= |caption= |currentowner=[[Panavision]] |producttype=[[Camera stabilizer]] |introduced= |country=United States |website= }}
'''Panaglide''' is a brand of [[camera stabilizer]] mounts for [[Movie camera|motion picture cameras]] made by [[Panavision]].<ref>[https://www.panavision.com/sites/default/files/docs/documentLibrary/1982%20Panavision%20Brochure.pdf Panavision]</ref><ref>[https://www.jukolart.us/cinematographic-systems/panavision-panaglide.html Jukolart.us]</ref><ref>[http://www.in70mm.com/newsletter/2002/67/panavision/pages/diffusion.htm In70mm.com]</ref>
The Panaglide steadies the camera operator's movement, allowing for a smooth shot.
The Panaglide was used in such films as ''[[Halloween (1978 film)|Halloween]]'' and [[Terrence Malick]]'s ''[[Days of Heaven]]'', which was the first film to use the Panaglide.<ref>[http://www.indiewire.com/2013/07/watch-test-footage-from-john-carpenters-halloween-using-steadicam-competitor-panaglide-95380/ IndieWire]</ref>
