'''Twinfield''' is an online [[financial accounting]] [[software]] package for [[small and medium enterprise]]s, produced and maintained by '''Twinfield International''', based in the [[Netherlands]].<ref>[http://www.twinfield.com Official website]</ref>  It is used by over 15,000 subscribers in 20 countries.<ref>[http://www.iia.ie/articles.asp?id=838 Irish Internet Association article]  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061021232803/http://www.iia.ie/articles.asp?id=838 |date=October 21, 2006 }}</ref>

The software is based on [[Software as a service]] (SaaS), so accounts can be accessed and analysed online, and the software is maintained by the provider, not the subscriber.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070930194042/http://www.vnunet.com/accountancyage/news/2149036/savings-accountants-move-online Savings see accountants move online], ''[[Accountancy Age]]'', 23 January 2006; [https://web.archive.org/web/20070930201140/http://www.vnunet.com/accountancyage/features/2161366/death-spreadsheet-SME-technology SME technology special: death of the spreadsheet], ''Accountancy Age'', 27 Jul 2006.</ref>

In 2005 Twinfield International received an Export Connection Award from [[Dutch Ministry of Economic Affairs]] for international focus and innovation.<ref>[http://www.computerpartner.nl/articles/6951 Exportprijs voor aanbieder online administratie], ComputerPartner, 25 November 2005 {{nl icon}} {{dead link|date=October 2014}}</ref>

